用形容词为描述一个名词，但是用副词为描述一个动词

形容词+ly
easy - easily (去y加ily)
quick - quickly
bad - badly

不规则的副词
fast - fast
good - well

He cooks good food
他做好的饭
He cooks food well
他做饭做得好

如果要比较两个不同的名词如何做某事，请使用“more更多”
I run quickly
我跑得快
I run more quickly* than you
我比你跑得更多快

*如果X只有一个音节，你可以在末尾加'er'而不是加'more'
I run quickly
我跑得快
I run quicker than you
我比你跑得更多快”"""),
("""Indefinite pronouns""", """Indefinite pronouns不定代词

everything 一切
something 某物
nothing 没有什么
anything 任何事物

everyone 每个人
someone 某人
no one 没有人
anyone 任何人

everywhere 到处
somewhere 某处
nowhere 无处
anywhere 任何地方"""),
("""All, Some, None, Any of them""", """...of them

用它来指代上述句子

all of them 他们都是
some of them 其中有一些
none of them 其中没有一个
any of them 其中任何一个
one of them 其中一个

In this sentence, "one of them" means "one of the 5 dogs"
There are 5 dogs in the room, and one of them is brown
房间里有5只狗，其中一只是棕色的"""),
("""Should, Had better, Ought to""", """Should, Had better, Ought to

Should和ought to都表示“应该”，但ought to不用于否定句或疑问句中
You should/ought to study
你应该学习
You shouldn't study
你不应该学习

Had better比“should/ought to强。 它强调如果你不做某事就会有负面的后果
You had better do your homework (or you will fail)
你最好做好功课（否则你会失败）
You'd better not do that (or you will get hurt)
你最好不要那样做（否则你会受伤"""),
("""Present Perfect Continuous""", """Present Perfect Continuous 现在完成进行时

Use this to talk about something you started doing before now and you are still doing

I've been studying math for two years
我学了两年数学(我仍然是)
I've been reading this book since 10am
我从上午 10 点开始读这本书(我仍然是)
I've been eating rice
我一直在吃米饭(我仍然是)"""),
("""Present Perfect vs Present Perfect Continuous""", """Present Perfect[PP] vs Present Perfect Continuous[PPC]

[PP] - I have read this book 我看过了这本书(已经读完了)
[PPC] - I have been reading this book 我一直在读这本书(还没读完了)"""),
("""Will, May, Might""", """Will, May, Might 将来时

These three words are used to talk about the future.

Will - 会
I will go to school
我会去学校
I won't go to school
我不会去学校
May/might - 可能会
I may/might go to school
我可能会去学校
I may/might not go to school
我可能不去学校"""),
("""Unless and If""", """Unless and If ’除非‘和’如果‘

这两个词用于谈论将来可能会发生的事情，但前提是先发生其他事情。

If - 如果
如果X发生，Y会发生
If it is raining, I will stay at home
如果下雨，我会呆在家里
If it isn't raining, I will go out
如果不下雨，我就出去

Unless - 除非
如果X不发生，Y会发生
Unless it is raining, I will go outside
除非下雨，否则我会出去""")),
