        (("""Future forms""", """Future tense forms

•If there is a future time in the sentence, or the future is obvious, you can use tenses that are not the future tense.

Present simple - The film [opens] in the UK on Friday
Future simple - History [will be made] later today
Going to verb - I'm [going to write] a book next year
Present continuous - I [am spending] three days in China next month"""),
("""Question tags""", """Question tags

•These are used to make sure what you just said is correct

It will rain (我告诉你什么会发生)
It will rain later, right? - (我觉得我说得对但是我想要证实)

She sings well, doesn't she?
You're going to the store, aren't you?
It's going to snow tomorrow, isn't it?"""),
("""Nor / Neither / So""", """Nor / Neither / So

•Use 'nor/neither' to agree with negative sentences

I don't like it.  Neither do I
我不喜欢那个东西。我也是
I don't like it.  Nor do I
我不喜欢那个东西。我也是

•Use 'so' to agree with positive sentences

I like it.  So do I
我喜欢那个东西。我也是"""),
("""Past Continuous vs Past Simple""", """Past continuous[PC] vs Past Simple[PS]

[PC] 有时长
It was raining
[PS] 发生得快
I ate breakfast

I ate breakast while it was raining
下雨的时候我吃了饭"""),
("""Used to""", """Used to

•Use this to talk about something you did a lot in the past but now you don't do it

I studied math (I did it and now I don't)
I used to study math (I did it often and now I don't)"""),
("""Second conditional""", """Would

•Use this to talk about something that is not real

Real: I have no money. I will die.
Fake: If I had a lot of money, I would not die

•The real sentence is what is true. The fake sentence is what is not true; it is hypothetical(虚拟的).

"If I had a lot of money" is not real; you are pretending(假装) it is real. And when you pretend something 
is real in the past, you can say what will be different in the present(现在).

•For fake sentences, you must use [if + past simple][would + present event]
[If + I had a lot of money], [I would + not die]

~~~I wish~~~
[I wish + past simple] is used when you say you want the fake to be real

I wish + I had money (I don't really have money, but I want to) """),
("""Passive simple""", """Passive 被

•Use the passive when:
what happens is more important than who does it
or you don't know who does it

The man opens the door
男人打开门

The door is opened (by the man)
门被（男人）打开
In this sentence, the most important thing is that the door is opened, not who opens it

动词  -> be动词 + 过去分词
open -> is opened
eat  -> is eaten"""),
("""Passive continous and perfect""", """Passive continous and perfect

--Passive Continuous--
•Used in the same way as the passive simple, but when something is happening now

Books are being written every day
人们每天都写书，但谁在写并不重要

--Passive Perfect--
•Used in the same way as the passive simple, but when something happens for a long time in the past and the time isn't important

Many books have been written
过去人们写过很多书，但谁写的并不重要"""),
("""Past perfect simple""", """Past perfect simple

•Used to talk about the past in the past
•The thing that happens first uses 'had done', and the thing that happens after uses the simple past

She had been there for two weeks when she died
在她死之前，她在那里呆了两个星期

I had just returned home when it started raining
我刚回家就开始下雨了

I had already done my homework when the phone rang
电话铃响时，我已经做完作业了"""),
("""Past perfect continuous""", """Past perfect continuous

•It is the same as the present continuous, but in the past

I [had been sleeping] for two hours when my phone rang
我已经睡了两个小时了，这时电话铃响了

He [had already been studying] for three hours when I arrived
我到达时，他已经学习了三个小时"""),
("""Reported statements""", """Reported statements

•Used to say what someone else said

•Many times we change the verb to the past tense
•Many times we use 'tell + 宾语' and 'say' with reported speech

• It is always in the past tense.  You must change the tenses like this:

present simple > past simple
He told me he wanted to eat noodles

present continuous > past continuous
He said he was eating noodles

past simple > past perfect
He said he has already eaten noodles

present perfect > past perfect
He said he has already eaten noodles

be going to > was/were going to
He told me he was going to eat noodles

can > could
He asked me if I could eat noodles

will > would
He asked me if I would eat noodles when I returned home"""),
("""Object + infinitive""", """Object + infinitive

•Some verbs (ask/want/tell) have a 宾语 and then a 不定式

...      动词  宾语      不定式
My dad [asked][me][to cook dinner]

I      [told][her][to sit down]

Tom   [wanted][me][to speak]"""),
("""Be allowed to / let""", """Be allowed to / let

•Used to talk about what other people say you can(可以)/can't(不可以) do

I'm [not allowed to] watch that film
我[不可以]看那部电影
有'be allowed to' 的句子不需要说谁不让

My mom [let's] me eat candy
我的妈妈[让]我吃糖
有'let'的句子需要说谁让"""),
("""Third conditional""", """Third conditional

•Used to talk about hypothetical(虚拟的) things in the past

had+过去分词...  would have+过去分词
If I had studied, I would have passed the exam
如果我学习了，我就会通过考试

If we had run, we wouldn't have missed the train
如果我们跑了，就不会误了火车""")),
